\name{fda_demo_data}
\alias{fda_demo_data}
\docType{data}
\title{Demo Data for Functional Data Analysis Workflows}
\format{
A list with three components:
\describe{
\item{weather_daily}{Daily weather curves for multiple simulated sites.}
\item{assessments}{One binary disease assessment per site with \code{wm} and
\code{wm_class}.}
\item{variable_specs}{A data frame of FDA variable names and display labels.}
}
}
\description{
A bundled dataset for the functional data analysis tutorial.
}
\details{
The data were created from the package's simulation functions and then bundled so
the FDA vignette can focus on interpretation, smoothing, interval testing, and
feature extraction.
}
\keyword{datasets}




